##  Cross-cutting (apply the same canonical fix in every dir)

 -  sha-hex decode `{sha.data, sha.data+20}` / `{v[0], v[0]+40}` → `sha1FromHex` + `a_head`/`a_rest` (CODE-016 funnel).
 -  `memcmp` for equality → `sha1Eq` / `u8csEq` / `u8csHasSuffix`.
 -  buffer-internals poke `((T**)buf)[2] = …` → `u8bFed` / `u8bShed` / typed reset-to-mark (never index a buffer's cells).
 -  hand-rolled Fork/Join `before=IdleHead; …feed…; {before,after}` → `u8sFork` / `u8sJoin` (or capture a gauge).
 -  separator scan `while (p<e && *p!='/') p++` → `u8csFind` + `a_head`/`a_rest`.
 -  `void *ctx` callback contexts are the sanctioned ABC closure idiom — NOT in scope; do not churn them.

